  yield hardening-summary ≡ "The adversarial hardening loop ran 5 iterations across 4 vulnerability-fix cycles. Starting from a 3-line naive login function, the code evolved into a 24-line hardened implementation covering: (1) safe dictionary access preventing KeyError crashes, (2) PBKDF2-HMAC-SHA256 password hashing with per-user salts, (3) account lockout after 5 failed attempts with 5-minute cooldown, and (4) constant-time response via dummy hash on nonexistent-user path. Each patch was verified against the specific exploit AND all previously accumulated regression tests, ensuring no fix re-introduced a previous vulnerability. The red-team found vulnerabilities in decreasing severity order (critical, critical, high, medium), demonstrating the adversarial loop's natural triage behavior. On iteration 5, the red-team yielded 'none' — no new in-scope vulnerability found."

